```

And used as, see [https://github.com/banaio/vue_js_samples/blob/master/vuex_accessing_nested_property_bug/src/components/HelloWorld.vue](https://github.com/banaio/vue_js_samples/blob/master/vuex_accessing_nested_property_bug/src/components/HelloWorld.vue),
the `level_3_broken` does not work, but the `level_3_working` seems to work:

```js
  computed: {
    ...mapGetters({
      level_3_broken: 'level_1.level_2.level_3',
    }),
    level_3_working() {
      return this.$store.getters['level_1']['level_2'].level_3;
    },
  },
```

